results.raw: Heavy Snow in Twin Cities on Friday at Minneapolis-St Paul Int'l Airport
results.title: Heavy Snow in Twin Cities on Friday

-Mq_78NVdL1RSzQT0vjj.text: Incident reported at Minneapolis-St Paul Int'l Airport.

-Mq_78Np4U3QLFQ901RY.text: The National Weather Service (NWS) has issued a Winter Storm Warning for Minneapolis and St. Paul that is expected to last until 6 a.m. on Saturday.

-Mq_7jElHFwe5zoxqkKN.text: Winter Storm Warnings are issued when at least 6" of snow is forecast to fall over a period of 12 hours.

nib.text:
Heavy snow is forecast across portions of the Twin Cities on Friday and into Saturday morning.

Between 8” and 12” of snow is expected to fall throughout Hennepin and Ramsey Counties.

The National Weather Service (NWS) has issued a Winter Storm Warning that will go into effect at 12 p.m. on Friday and will last until 6 a.m. on Saturday.

Snowy conditions could make travel difficult or impossible. Hazardous road conditions could impact evening commutes.

If travel is necessary, Minnesotans can obtain the latest road conditions by calling 5-1-1, or visiting [511mn.org](https://511mn.org/).
